data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Monday’s magnitude 4.4 quake that rattled Southern California is believed to have struck on a well-known and dangerous fault system known as the Puente Hills thrust fault system.

The Norton Simon in Pasadena may get overshadowed by LACMA, MOCA and the Broad, but its 12,000-piece collection is one of SoCal’s best. Our critic offers a shortlist of don’t-miss works.

Minutes before first period, staff at Jordan High School in Watts reported a loud noise and a plume of smoke emanating from the metal recycling yard next door.

Janet Jackson says she is related to Stevie Wonder, Tracy Chapman and Samuel L. Jackson, in addition to her musical siblings.

Walker Buehler had a tough night in first start back from injury, and the Dodgers committed three errors in a loss to Milwaukee.

Mohammad Abu Al-Qumsan lost his children, wife, and mother-in-law in an Israeli strike that hit a Gaza Strip apartment building while he was away.
